Place a foil-lined #baking sheet{} on top rack (for 4 servings, place 2 foil-lined baking sheets on top and middle racks) and preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, peel, and thinly slice @red onion{1}(thinly sliced). Drain @pineapple{4%oz} over a small #bowl{}, reserving juice. Stir one-quarter of the onion, half the @red wine vinegar{2 1/2%tsp} (you'll use the rest later), and a pinch of @salt{pinch} into bowl with juice. Set aside.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{drizzle} in a large #pan{} over medium heat. Add remaining onion and cook, stirring and adding splashes of water as needed to prevent sticking, until softened, ~{6-8%minutes}.

While onion cooks, halve, core, and very thinly slice @long green pepper{1}(thinly sliced into strips). Toss in a second small bowl with a small drizzle of @olive oil{small drizzle}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Dice @fresh mozzarella{4%oz} into 1⁄2-inch pieces.

Open package of @Italian chicken sausage mix{9%oz} and drain off any excess liquid; season all over with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Heat a drizzle of oil in a second large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken sausage; cook, stirring frequently, until cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Once cooked onion is softened, increase heat under pan to medium high. Add pineapple; cook, stirring, until pineapple is lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in remaining @red wine vinegar{2 1/2%tsp}. Cook, stirring, until onion and pineapple are caramelized and jammy, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Turn off heat and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Brush or rub each @flatbreads{2} with a small drizzle of @oil{drizzle}. Remove prepared baking sheet from oven; carefully place flatbreads on sheet.

> For 4 servings, divide flatbreads between both prepared sheets.

Evenly spread flatbreads with @BBQ sauce{4%tbsp}, then top with caramelized onion and pineapple, green pepper, @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}, and mozzarella. Top flatbreads with chicken sausage.

Return flatbreads to top rack until cheese melts and edges are golden brown, ~{10-12%minutes}.

> For 4 servings, return to top and middle racks; swap rack positions halfway through baking.

Transfer flatbreads to a #cutting board{} and top with pickled onion (draining first) to taste. Slice into quarters, divide between plates, and serve.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.